text: Shubuta Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Shubuta is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "smoke, smoky, smoking". Variant names are "Bok Shubuta", "Cheehootee Creek", "Chobota", "Shoboti Creek", and "Shoebootee Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Clarke County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Jasper County, Mississippi
title: Shubuta Creek
